      "note": "12 EW_CAPTURE runs on this box (unlike G1's dense-pan-zoom-1000) NEVER observed a dropped/jank frame here — p95/maxms floor at the ~16.7-16.8ms vsync tick every run, no bimodal split. Recorded values are the worst OBSERVED across those 12 runs (16.8ms), not a cherry-picked minimum, so this baseline is already the honest typical-worst for this scenario/hardware — same discipline as the dense scenario's note, different (cleaner) observed reality: seedGrid spreads shapes off-screen so ShapeLayer's own per-shape render cost stays near-zero here, isolating Selection.tsx's O(selection-size) overlay cost as the only added work, and on this hardware that cost alone doesn't push a frame past the vsync floor. The +15%x2x gate (=38.64ms) still protects against a REAL regression in that overlay cost; it just means, unlike dense, this scenario's maxms isn't expected to be a noisy signal in practice."
